Attention Fusion for Severity Analysis. The availability of data from different media sources has encouraged researchers to explore and leverage the potential boost in performance by combining unimodal classifiers trained on individual modalities [5, 27]. Here, we use attention fusion to combine the feature interpretations from the text and image modalities for the severity analysis module [12, 26]. The idea of attention fusion is to attend particular input features as compared to others while predicting the output class. The features, i.e., the outputs of the penultimate layer or the layer before the softmax, of the text and image models are concatenated. This is followed by a softmax layer to learn the attention weights for each feature dimension, i.e., the attention weight \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
